==Chapter 1==
===Talking to King Narnode Shareen===
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Adventurer! It is good to see you again.
* '''Player:''' And you too, King. How fares the tree?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' The tree? It is fine, as it has always been since we foiled Glough's plans.
* '''Player:''' Good. What ever did happen to Glough?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Oh, I forced him to resign. I have now appointed a new Head Tree Guardian, Daero. He is learning quickly and serves me well.
* '''Player:''' King, you look worried. Is anything the matter?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Nothing in particular ... Well actually, yes - there is.
* '''Player:''' What is it?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Well, do you remember Glough's ship building facilities in Karamja?
* '''Player:''' Yes, they were on the eastern coast. What of them?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' After you defeated Glough's demon I sent an envoy of my Royal Guard, the 10th squad, to oversee the decommission of the shipyard. They were ordered to use force if necessary.
* '''Player:''' I see ... Were they successful?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' I ... I don't know. I have heard nothing from them. I do not even know if they reached the shipyard!
* '''Player:''' It is a long way...
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' But I need to know what happened. These are elite soldiers - their disappearance cannot simply be ignored. I cannot wait any longer.
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' And so I ask you: would you visit Glough's old shipyard in Karamja and find out if the 10th squad ever managed to reach?
* {{tselect|Start the Monkey Madness I quest?}}
* {{topt|Yes.}}
** '''Player:''' Ok, I'll do it.
** {{tbox|pic=Gnome royal seal detail.png|Narnode hands you a copy of the Royal Seal.}}
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Thank you very much. You may need this Royal Seal to identify yourself as my envoy.
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Please report to me as soon as you have any information.
** {{tact|end}}
** {{qact|Monkey Madness: Chapter 1<br> In which our hero finds themselves drawn back into Glough's web of deception and deceit.}}
* {{topt|No.}}
** '''Player:''' I'm afraid I am too busy right now.
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' As you wish. Return to me when you have the time.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to King Narnode again after previously declining to help===
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Are you ready to investigate the shipyard for me?
* '''Player:''' What do I have to do?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Go to Glough's old shipyard on the eastern coast of Karamja. Find out what happened to the 10th squad of my Royal Guard.
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' As I said, they were sent to oversee the decommission of the ship building facilities, but I have heard nothing from them.
* {{tselect|Start the Monkey Madness I quest?}}
* {{topt|Yes.}}
** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|No.}}
** {{tact|above}}

===Talking to King Narnode after starting the quest===
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Welcome back, adventurer.
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|What am I meant to do?}}
** '''Player:''' What am I meant to do?
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Go to Glough's old shipyard on the eastern coast of Karamja. Find out what happened to the 10th squad of my Royal Guard.
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' As I said, they were sent to oversee the decommission of the ship building facilities, but I have heard nothing from them.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|How did the 10th squad travel?}}
** '''Player:''' How did the 10th squad travel?
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' They would have each flown a Gnome Glider.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|I'll be back later.}}
** '''Player:''' I'll be back later.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to King Narnode after losing the royal seal===
* {{tmissing}}

===Trying to enter the Ship Yard===
* '''Shipyard worker:''' Hey you! What are you up to?
* '''Player:''' I'm trying to open the gate!
* '''Shipyard worker:''' I can see that! Why?
* '''Player:''' I am on a special mission for King Narnode of the Gnomes.
* '''Shipyard worker:''' Narnode? I don't believe you. He wouldn't send a human!
* '''Player:''' Well, he did...
* '''Shipyard worker:''' Tough.
* {{tcond|If the player doesn't have the royal seal:}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the royal seal:}}
** '''Player:''' Look, I have the Gnome Royal Seal. <!--You can end the dialogue here after and he'll just start letting you in, couldnt get the they/them dialogue-->
** {{tbox|pic=Gnome royal seal detail.png|You show the shipyard worker the Royal Seal.}}
** '''Shipyard worker:''' Wow. I haven't seen one of these since...
** '''Player:''' Since when?
** '''Shipyard worker:''' ... since Glough used to visit.
** '''Shipyard worker:''' Anyway. Please step inside, [Sir/Miss].
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the foreman===
* {{tcond|First time:}}
** '''Player:''' Hello there.
** '''Foreman:''' Hello. Do I know you? You seem remarkably familiar...
** '''Player:''' Erm, no you don't know me.
** '''Foreman:''' If you say so. Anyway, what do you want?
** {{tact|continues}}
* '''Player:''' Have you seen any of King Narnode's Royal Guard recently? They were meant to be doing ... some work in the area.
* '''Foreman:''' I wouldn't know anything about that. You should see Caranock.
* '''Player:''' Who is Caranock?
* '''Foreman:''' Our Gnome Liaison Officer.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to G.L.O. Caranock===
* '''Player:''' Hello!
* '''G.L.O. Caranock:''' Who are you? Did Glough send you?
* '''Player:''' Glough? No. He has been forced to resign by the King.
* '''G.L.O. Caranock:''' Forced to resign??
* '''Player:''' He was plotting to start a war between Gnomes and humankind.
* '''Player:''' Anyway, I am here on a separate mission. I am investigating the mysterious disappearance of the 10th squad of King Narnode's Royal Guard. They were to carry out some work in the area.
* '''G.L.O. Caranock:''' Royal Guard? I know nothing about them. Absolutely nothing.
* '''Player:''' You have no idea why they mysteriously disappeared?
* '''G.L.O. Caranock:''' None whatsoever. What were they here to do?
* '''Player:''' They were to oversee the decommission of the shipyard.
* '''G.L.O. Caranock:''' Decommission the shipyard... I see. Well, we have had some seriously strong southerly winds of late. They may have been blown off course during flight.
* '''G.L.O. Caranock:''' I shall personally see to the decommission. You should report to the King immediately.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Caranock again===
* '''G.L.O. Caranock:''' Why are you still here? You should report immediately to the King!
* {{tact|end}}

===Returning to King Narnode===
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Welcome back, adventurer.
* '''Player:''' Hello. I investigated the shipyard.
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Thank you for doing this. What did you find?
* '''Player:''' I met a Gnome who goes by the name of Caranock. Do you recognise it?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' The name sounds a little familiar, but it is nobody I know personally.
* '''Player:''' He calls himself a Gnome Liaison Officer. He seemed a little... odd
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Never mind that - did you find anything out about my 10th squad?
* '''Player:''' Caranock suggested they were blown off course by extreme southern winds.
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Do you believe him?
* '''Player:''' I don't have any other information right now.
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Very well. I will now prepare some orders. You must convey them to my new High Tree Guardian, Daero. <!--Short delay after as he writes the notes-->
* {{mes|Narnode begins to write strange glyphs on a scroll of paper.}}
* {{tbox|pic=Narnode's orders detail.png|Narnode hands you some handwritten orders.}}
* '''Player:''' Where will I find Daero?
* '''King Narnode Shareen:''' You will find him attending to business somewhere on the Grand Tree.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to King Narnode again===
* {{tcond|If you still have the orders:}}
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' How goes the mission?
** '''Player:''' I'm still working on it...
* {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If you lost the orders:}}
** '''Player:''' Excuse me...
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Yes, adventurer?
** '''Player:''' You know those orders you gave me -
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' You've lost them?
** '''Player:''' Yes - how did you know?
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Oh, it often happens. Luckily I had the foresight to write in a secret code on self-destructing paper.
** '''King Narnode Shareen:''' Here, take a another.
** {{mes|Narnode begins to write strange glyphs on a scroll of paper.}}
** {{tbox|pic=Narnode's orders detail.png|Narnode hands you some handwritten orders.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Speaking to Daero===
* '''Player:''' Are you Daero?
* '''Daero:''' Indeed I am - and you are?
* '''Player:''' I am an adventurer. I am currently in the service of your King.
* '''Daero:''' I see. You must be the individual who helped defeat my predecessor Glough. I hope you'll find me a more honest replacement.
* '''Player:''' I have been asked to give you orders from King Narnode.
* '''Daero:''' Well hand them over here then.
* {{tcond|If you don't have the orders:}}
** '''Player:''' However, I appear to have lost them...
** '''Daero:''' Well you'd better retrieve them as soon as possible. Our enemies may extract sensitive information from them.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If you don't have the orders:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Narnode's orders detail.png|You hand King Narnode's orders to Daero.}}
** {{tact|continues}}
* '''Daero:''' It is written in an old military code. Bear with me whilst I decode this.
* {{mes|Daero begins decoding the orders.}}
* '''Daero:''' I hope you feel like a quest adventurer ...
* '''Player:''' Why is that?
* '''Daero:''' ... because you are going to get one.
* '''Player:''' Tell me what the orders say!
* '''Daero:''' Given your recent performance of uncovering and neutralising a threat at the very extremes of the Gnome hierarchy, the King has decreed that you are to undertake a reconnaisance mission.
* '''Player:''' Where to?
* '''Daero:''' You are to be taken far to the south of Karamja, further than any Gnome has purposely travelled before. You are to investigate Caranock's claim that Garkor's squad were blown off course.
* '''Daero:''' You must really have impressed the King in the past.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Talk about the journey...}}
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|What lies to the south of Karamja?}}
*** '''Player:''' What lies to the south of Karamja?
*** '''Daero:''' We do not know. Initial reports spoke of a large atoll populated by monkeys.
*** '''Player:''' Monkeys? Like on Karamja?
*** '''Daero:''' From what I have heard, not quite like those monkeys...
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|How will I travel?}}
*** '''Player:''' How will I travel?
*** '''Daero:''' It is my responsibility to make arrangements for your mission. We will shortly visit a colleague of mine who will be accompanying you.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Are you coming with me?}}
*** '''Player:''' Are you coming with me?
*** '''Daero:''' I am afraid not. I must remain here to safeguard the Grand Tree. I will assign a Gnome agent to travel with you.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Return to previous menu}} <!--0000ff Blue text-->
* {{topt|Talk about the 10th squad...}}
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Why did the King send a squad of the Royal Guard?}}
*** '''Player:''' Why did the King send a squad of the Royal Guard?
*** '''Daero:''' The Royal Guard is composed of particularly elite soldiers who have proven themselves in battle. They are duty bound to protect the Grand Tree its King and his interests.
*** '''Daero:''' In the face of danger, they can more than take care of themselves.
*** '''Player:''' So the King worries we have come across an equally formidable foe?
*** '''Daero:''' He worries about this, yes.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Who is Garkor?}}
*** '''Player:''' Who is Garkor?
*** '''Daero:''' Sergeant Garkor holds the command of the 10th squad. As a soldier, he is extremely able. If his men are in trouble, he will be tirelessly working to save them.
*** '''Daero:''' You should aim to make contact with him.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Why are the 10th squad so famous?}}
*** '''Player:''' Why are the 10th squad so famous?
*** '''Daero:''' They are, as you humans might say, the best of the best. As well as Sergeant Garkor, they have in their company a High Mage, two sappers and battle hardened foot soldiers.
*** '''Player:''' What is a sapper?
*** '''Daero:''' You might consider the role as that of an engineer. Or perhaps of a munitions expert.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Return to previous menu}}
* {{topt|Talk about Caranock}}
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Who is Caranock?}}
*** '''Player:''' Who is Caranock?
*** '''Daero:''' I have never heard of him. According to the report you made to the King, he is the Gnome Liaison Officer at the eastern Karamja shipyard.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|What is a Gnome Liaison Officer?}}
*** '''Player:''' What is a Gnome Liaison Officer?
*** '''Daero:''' It was a position Glough introduced. Gnome Liaison Officers are in general responsible for coordinating activities between Gnomes and other beings in our remote operations.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|I'm not so sure about Caranock...}}
*** '''Player:''' I'm not so sure about Caranock...
*** '''Daero:''' In what way?
*** '''Player:''' I do not know. He just seemed a little suspicious. He was very keen to see me leave.
*** '''Daero:''' I do not know him; he is from before my time. Glough would presumably have hand picked him.
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Return to previous menu}}
* {{topt|Leave...}}
** '''Player:''' Let us go then.
** '''Daero:''' I must first introduce you to a colleague of mine who will be accompanying you on your mission.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Who is it?}}
*** '''Player:''' Who is it?
*** '''Daero:''' His name is Flight Commander Waydar.
*** '''Daero:''' We must go now and meet Waydar. For security reasons I must ask you to wear a blindfold.
*** {{tbox|pic=Right eye patch detail.png|You wear the blindfold Daero hands you.}}
*** {{qact|The player is transported to the Underground Military Glider Hangar.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|I work better on my own...}}
*** '''Player:''' I work better on my own...
*** '''Daero:''' Tough. You will be working with Flight Commander Waydar.
*** '''Daero:''' We must go now and meet Waydar. For security reasons I must ask you to wear a blindfold.
*** {{tbox|pic=Right eye patch detail.png|You wear the blindfold Daero hands you.}}
*** {{qact|The player is transported to the Underground Military Glider Hangar.}}
*** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Daero again before giving him the orders===
* '''Player:''' I have been asked to give you orders from King Narnode.
* '''Daero:''' Well hand them over here then.
* {{tact|above}}

===The Underground Hangar===
====Talking to Waydar before Daero====
* '''Waydar:''' Sorry, I am not authorised to talk to you.
* {{tact|end}}

====Interacting with the panel before being tasked with aligning it====
* {{tbox|You do not know what you are doing.}}
* {{tact|end}}

====Speaking to Daero in the underground hangar====
* '''Daero:''' Welcome, adventurer, to the Underground Military Glider Hangar.
* '''Player:''' Wow! Why would Gnomes need such a place?
* '''Daero:''' We do not, if the truth be told. This hangar was part of Glough's contingency planning. Had the attacks by land and sea failed, he would have turned to air.
* '''Daero:''' It is fortunate indeed that you managed to expose him. The military gliders in this hangar are a prototype for a much refined version of the standard variety we currently use.
* '''Daero:''' Let me introduce you to Flight Commander Waydar.
* '''Daero:''' Flight Commander Waydar, I would like you to meet [player name].
* '''Waydar:''' Greetings High Tree Guardian.
* '''Waydar:''' And greetings to you too, visitor.
* '''Daero:''' Not just any old visitor Waydar; this is the person who exposed Glough and defeated his demon.
* '''Waydar:''' I see. Well, there are no more demons left here.
* '''Daero:''' Quite. [He is/She is/They are] now on a secret mission for the King.
* '''Daero:''' As you know, the 10th squad went missing during their mission to decommission the eastern shipyard of Karamja.
* '''Daero:''' We still do not know what happened, but evidence suggests they were blown far off course to the south.
* '''Waydar:''' Their standard gliders must have fallen prey to the tropical weather.
* '''Daero:''' When reinitialisation has been completed, you are to fly to the south of Karamja with [player name] and accompany [him/her/them] on the mission.
* '''Waydar:''' We are no closer to reinitialising sir - the code is too hard. It is likely the only person who could do it is Glough.
* '''Daero:''' That Gnome is never stepping foot in this hangar again. He always was and still is a menace. Do you understand me?
* '''Waydar:''' Yes sir.
* '''Daero:''' Very well. Notify me when you have managed to reinitialise.
* '''Daero:''' [player name], you will have to wait till reinitialisation is complete.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Daero outside of the bunker====
* '''Daero:''' Hello again, adventurer. Would you like to return to the hangar?
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Yes}}
** '''Player:''' Yes please.
** {{tbox|pic=Right eye patch detail.png|You wear the blindfold Daero hands you.}}
** {{qact|The player is transported to the Underground Military Glider Hangar.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No}}
** '''Player:''' Not right now, thanks.
** '''Daero:''' Very well. Return to me when you do.
** {{tact|end}}

====Selecting Travel at Daero when in the hangar====
* '''Player:''' How do I leave?
* '''Daero:''' There is a teleporter round the corner. You must use this.
* {{tact|end}}

====Searching the crate of spare controls====
* {{tbox|pic=Spare controls detail.png|This crate is full of ...  spare controls!}}
* {{tselect|Do you wish to take one?}}
* {{topt|Yes}}
** {{tact|receives=Spare controller}}
* {{topt|No}}
** {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Daero in the hangar before completing the puzzle====
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Where is the hangar?}}
** '''Player:''' Where is the hangar?
** '''Daero:''' We try to ensure the location of the hangar remains a secret. If you must know something, then know that it lies directly beneath the Gnomeball pitch. However, I cannot reveal the location of its entrance.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|How do I leave?}}
** '''Player:''' How do I leave?
** '''Daero:''' There is a teleporter round the corner.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|How do I return here later?}}
** '''Player:''' How do I return later?
** '''Daero:''' Come and find me on the Grand Tree. I will probably be at the bar.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What is reinitialisation?}}
** '''Player:''' What is reinitialisation?
** '''Daero:''' Glough left a code on the facility which periodically needs to be entered if we wish to maintain the supply of power.
** '''Daero:''' Without going through this process of reinitiliasation, we cannot power the mechanism which deploys the millitary gliders.
** {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Wayday before completing the puzzle====
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|What are military gliders?}}
** '''Player:''' What are military gliders?
** '''Waydar:''' As Daero said, they are a prototype for a new version of glider. They are reinforced yet are built out of lighter materials. They can fly much faster and for longer.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Why are the gliders folded against the wall?}}
** '''Player:''' Why are the gliders folded against the wall?
** '''Waydar:''' It is the most compact way to store them. Unfortunately, they will remain like that until they are powered. We can only fully power the hangar when reinitialisation has been completed.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|When will reinitialisation be completed?}}
** '''Player:''' When will reinitialisation be completed?
** '''Waydar:''' I cannot be sure. It is a difficult code; it may happen the next instant - then again it may not.
** '''Waydar:''' You could even have a go at solving the code yourself.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Where is the reinitialisation code?}}
** '''Player:''' Where is the reinitialisation code?
** '''Waydar:''' The code must be entered at the red control panel just by the wall over there.
** {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Glough====
* '''Player:''' Hello?
* '''Glough:''' You look frustrated, human.
* '''Player:''' I've been told to wait for reinitialisation of the hangar. They mentioned your name.
* '''Glough:''' Of course they would. I'm the only one who knows how to do it.
* '''Player:''' This is really quite embarrassing, but...
* '''Glough:''' Let me guess, you need my help...
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|Yes, I suppose I do.}}
** '''Player:''' Yes, I suppose I do.
** '''Glough:''' I am able to remotely reinitialise...
** '''Player:''' But... ?
** '''Glough:''' It will cost you...
** '''Player:''' How much?
** '''Glough:''' Oh... just a measly 200,000 coins. Yes, I think that will do me nicely.
** {{tcond|If the player doesn't have 200,000 coins on them}}
*** '''Player:''' I don't have that kind of money on me right now.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has at least 200,000 coins on them}}
*** {{tselect|Select an option}}
*** {{topt|Ok then. You win again, Glough.}}
**** '''Player:''' Ok then. You win again, Glough.
**** '''Glough:''' It's been a pleasure doing business with you.
**** '''Player:''' Indeed. I wish I could say the same for you.
**** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|That's outrageous!}}
**** '''Player:''' That's outrageous!
**** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No, I'd rather skin a monkey than take your help!}}
** '''Player:''' No, I'd rather skin a monkey than take your help!
** '''Glough:''' You don't know how to do that yet!
** {{tact|end}}

====Speaking to Daero in the underground hangar after the puzzle is complete====
* '''Daero:''' Well done, adventurer. You have managed to break Glough's code. Now the process of reinitialisation is complete, you can truly begin your journey into the unknown. 
* '''Player:''' I've had some practice in the past.
* '''Daero:''' You are clearly a human of many talents.
* '''Daero:''' Flight Commander Waydar, now that reinitialisation is complete, I order you to fly to the south of Karamja with [player name]
* '''Waydar:''' Yes sir.
* '''Daero:''' You are to safeguard [him/her/them] on this potentially dangerous mission.
* '''Waydar:''' Understood.
* '''Daero:''' [player name], speak to Waydar when you are ready to leave.
* '''Daero:''' And ... good luck.
* {{tact|end}}

====Upon solving the puzzle====
* {{tbox|As you slide the final piece into place you begin to hear a low rumbling sound...}}
* {{qact|A cutscene plays as the screen shakes, showing the military gliders unfolding.}}

===Speaking to Waydar after solving the puzzle===
* '''Waydar:''' Well done on breaking the code. You should speak to the High Tree Guardian.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Daero after solving the puzzle====
* '''Daero:''' Well done, adventurer. You have managed to break Glough's code. Now the process of reinitialisation is complete, you can truly begin your journey into the unknown.
* '''Player:''' I've had some practice in the past.
* '''Daero:''' You are clearly a human of many talents.
* '''Daero:''' Flight Commander Waydar, now that reinitialisation is complete, I order you to fly to the south of Karamja with [player name].
* '''Waydar:''' Yes sir.
* '''Daero:''' You are to safeguard [him/her/them] on this potentially dangerous mission.
* '''Waydar:''' Understood.
* '''Daero:''' [player name], speak to Waydar when you are ready to leave.
* '''Daero:''' And ... good luck.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Daero again====
* '''Daero:''' Speak to Waydar when you are ready to leave.
* {{tact|end}}

====Travelling with Waydar====
* '''Waydar:''' You should stock up well on food before our journey. I can carry only enough provisions for myself.
* '''Waydar:''' I'd be careful of the local fauna too - I've heard the bite is far worse than any noise they make.
* '''Waydar:''' Do you wish to fly right now?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Yes}}
** '''Player:''' Yes, let's go.
** '''Waydar:''' As you wish.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No}}
** '''Player:''' Not yet. I'll be back later.
** {{tact|end}}

===Landing on Crash Island===
====Speaking to Waydar on Crash Island====
* '''Player:''' Where are we?
* '''Waydar:''' I am not sure. We appear to have landed where the 10th squad crashed. The number of gnome gliders is correct. Unfortunately for them, it appears that none of their gliders survived the collision.
* '''Player:''' Did our glider survive?
* '''Waydar:''' Of course.
* {{tact|end}}

====Speaking to Lumdo====
* '''Lumdo:''' Who are you two?
* '''Player:''' We are on a mission for King Narnode Shareen. I am [player name] and this is Flight Commander Waydar.
* '''Lumdo:''' What business do you have here?
* '''Player:''' We are to investigate the disappearance of the 10th squad of the Royal Guard. Am I right in suspecting that you, Lumdo, are a member of the 10th squad?
* '''Lumdo:''' I might be. Do you have any way to prove that you are who you say are?{{sic}}
* {{tcond|If the player still has the royal seal:}}
** '''Player:''' I have the Gnome Royal Seal.
** {{tbox|pic=Gnome royal seal detail.png|You show Lumdo the Royal Seal.}}
** '''Lumdo:''' I see. Sorry for my distrust.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|Otherwise:}}
** '''Player:''' We flew here on a military gnome glider. Is that not proof enough?
** '''Lumdo:''' I suppose it is. Sorry for my distrust.
** {{tact|continues}}
* '''Player:''' So are you Lumdo of the 10th squad?
* '''Lumdo:''' I am indeed -
* '''Player:''' Where are the rest of your squad? Where is your Sergeant?
* '''Lumdo:''' Let me begin at the beginning, human.
